latestPosts.caption:
Thank you 🙏🏻

Honestly, back in 2022, we came to the Cosmo Awards as nominees in the travel category without any real knowledge of what the industry or working in it would be like. And we were torn apart and left so anxious, that we never wanted to step foot into events or places with too many people again, afraid that we would be treated the way we were. And don’t get us wrong—we still feel that feeling at times. But years later, when we look back at everything we’ve done and worked on to reach where we are today, we feel so proud of each other. Knowing that we’re stronger now and that nothing can bring us down fills us with so much confidence. Here’s to staying “young & wild & free!”

Of course, none of this would have been possible without our families—who, knowing how tough it must have been to accept us in the first place, now cheer us on from the frontlines. To our friends, who have faced their own challenges but have never stepped back from supporting us, our team, who handles all our tantrums and yet professionally supports in ways nobody else can, and to our 👼well-wishers and 🩷homies—knowing that many of you have never physically met us or fully known us but still manifest the best for us makes us want to be a better human every-frickin-day!

This one’s for all of you who continue to amplify the LGBTQIA+ voice, with the hope that someday, we won’t need a separate category at all—because the LGBTQIA+ voice will resonate everywhere, unapologetically.
Sharing this joy with our fellow nominees, who have always been a constant source of strength and inspiration: @sanskari_satan and @trinetra 

🫂 @cosmoindia @pratishtha_dobhal @suneetvarmaofficial

latestPosts.caption:
Mini Vlog of Day 2 in Meghalaya 

We couldn’t go for the Cherry Blossom festival due to the crowd that we heard were gathering there, and so headed to Wards lake to experience our first cherry blossom! After which we made our way to the infamous police bazaar for some “pate-pooja” & thrifting that all of you said we CANNOT miss….shall we say, we were not let down 🔥

People of Meghalaya are sooo helpful and sweet! Can’t wait to experience more of this magic!
